<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,267,680]" box="[197,1261,345,371]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[289,423,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 42" captionStartId="6.[151,273,1925,1949]" captionTargetBox="[207,1412,310,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,279,1900]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 42. Striatanus erectus sp. nov. 31. habitus, dorsal view; 32. habitus, lateral view; 33. face; 34. male pygofer, lateral view; 35. aedeagus, ventral view; 36. aedeagus, lateral view; 37. forewing; 38. hindwing; 39. subgenital plate; 40. connective and style; 41. style; 42. pygofer ventral process, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Figs 31, 32</figureCitation>
) less elongate, distinctly shorter than pronotum and scutellum together.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,267,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[375,463,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 42" captionStartId="6.[151,273,1925,1949]" captionTargetBox="[207,1412,310,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,279,1900]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 42. Striatanus erectus sp. nov. 31. habitus, dorsal view; 32. habitus, lateral view; 33. face; 34. male pygofer, lateral view; 35. aedeagus, ventral view; 36. aedeagus, lateral view; 37. forewing; 38. hindwing; 39. subgenital plate; 40. connective and style; 41. style; 42. pygofer ventral process, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[432,463,384,410]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
) in lateral view with apex rounded; ventral process (
<figureCitation box="[1095,1233,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 42" captionStartId="6.[151,273,1925,1949]" captionTargetBox="[207,1412,310,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,279,1900]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 42. Striatanus erectus sp. nov. 31. habitus, dorsal view; 32. habitus, lateral view; 33. face; 34. male pygofer, lateral view; 35. aedeagus, ventral view; 36. aedeagus, lateral view; 37. forewing; 38. hindwing; 39. subgenital plate; 40. connective and style; 41. style; 42. pygofer ventral process, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Figs 34, 42</figureCitation>
) strongly curved dorsad, apical part tapered apically, with apex somewhat truncate. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1093,1181,422,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 42" captionStartId="6.[151,273,1925,1949]" captionTargetBox="[207,1412,310,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,279,1900]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 42. Striatanus erectus sp. nov. 31. habitus, dorsal view; 32. habitus, lateral view; 33. face; 34. male pygofer, lateral view; 35. aedeagus, ventral view; 36. aedeagus, lateral view; 37. forewing; 38. hindwing; 39. subgenital plate; 40. connective and style; 41. style; 42. pygofer ventral process, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191446/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[1150,1181,422,448]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56" value="35.0">35</number>
</figureCitation>
) strongly posteriorly produced basally; apical half of aedeagal shaft in lateral view nearly straight, gonopore subapical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1225,499,526]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,267,680]" box="[197,1225,499,526]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,342,499,525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="56">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name of this species is derived from the nearly straight aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
